		<div id="comment_body_64431360"><p><div class="quote"><p>Bytedance isn't necessarily foreign either.  60% of its shareholders are basically US shareholders.</p></div><p>Which doesn&rsquo;t matter even one bit, given that the 1% share the CCP has is a <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Golden_share" title="wikipedia.org">golden share</a> [wikipedia.org] that trumps the rest of the shares. For all intents and purposes, it&rsquo;s under the thumb of the CCP and thus its US operations are subject to Congressional oversight.</p></div>
	</div>

	<div class="commentSub" id="comment_sub_64431360">

</div>
